## Context
Wave-1 move of the code reorg epic (tracker `0240`). Relocate the Phase-2
figure-producing **entry points** — `plot_*` and `export_*` — into
`scripts/figures/`. Only Tier-3 entry points (per the 0254 audit) move; any
`plot_*`/`export_*` file that is imported by another script stays flat (Tier-2)
or was already extracted by 0254.

## Depends on 0253 + 0254
- `0253` installs the relative source-root path model, so a file under
  `scripts/figures/` still resolves `from utils import …`.
- `0254` publishes the definitive Tier-2 (stays-flat) vs Tier-3 (moves) list —
  the contract for exactly which files move here.

## Relevant files
- `scripts/plot_*.py`, `scripts/export_*.py` — the Tier-3 subset (per 0254)
- `docs/repo-layout.md` — the Tier-2/Tier-3 audit table (0254)
- `Makefile` + `scripts/analysis/*.mk` — figure/table target script paths to repoint
- `tests/test_layering.py` — layering guard (a plotter never imports a compute driver the wrong way)

## Actions
1. `git mv` each Tier-3 `plot_*` / `export_*` entry point into `scripts/figures/`.
2. Repoint every Make target script path (`scripts/plot_x.py` →
   `scripts/figures/plot_x.py`). Imports need no edit (flat module names via the
   path model).
3. Leave every Tier-2 library module flat at `scripts/` root.

## Test
- `make -n` for one figure target and one export target yields the same prereq
  graph — only the `scripts/figures/…` path segment changes.
- The moved entry points import + run under `PYTHONPATH=scripts:libs/openalex-corpus/src`.
- `make check` green; figure outputs byte-identical before/after (pure move).

## Invariants
- Only Tier-3 entry points move; Tier-2 library modules stay flat.
- No top-level `src/`; no `python -m`; flat module names unchanged.
- Layering (architecture.md rule 4): a compute module never imports a plotter.
- One logical move per PR (this ticket = the figures move only).

## Exit criteria
- All Tier-3 `plot_*`/`export_*` entry points live under `scripts/figures/`.
- Every Make script path repointed; no dangling reference.
- `make check` and `make clean && make all` green; figures byte-identical.

